      "part_type": "Hadith",
      "path": "/books/al-kafi:7:3:42:1",
      "text": [
        " قَالَ أَمِيرُ الْمُؤْمِنِينَ ( عليه السلام ) لَا قَطْعَ فِي رِيشٍ يَعْنِي الطَّيْرَ كُلَّهُ ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.hubeali": [
          "Ali Bin Ibrahim, from his father, from Al Nowfaly, from Al Sakuny, ",
          "(It has been narrated) from Abu Abdullah<sup>asws</sup> having said: ‘Amir Al-Momineen<sup>asws</sup> said: ‘(There would be) no cutting-off (the hand) with regards to a feather, meaning the whole bird’."
        ]
      }
